Package: sviBuildr
Type: Package
Title: Downloads the Social Vulnerability Index for use in R
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person(
        "Sebastian",
        "Rowan",
        email="sebastian.rowan@unh.edu",
        role=c("aut", "cre"))
URL: https://github.com/sebastianrowan/sviBuildr
Description: R package to download the required census data and calculate the 
    social vulnerability index (SVI) according to the methodology published by
    the US CDC's Agency for Toxic Substances and Disease Registry (ATSDR)
    (<https://www.atsdr.cdc.gov/placeandhealth/svi/index.html>). This package
    allows users to calculate the SVI for any study region within the US.
    sviBuildr utilizes the tidycensus package
    (<https://github.com/walkerke/tidycensus>) to interface with the US Census
    Bureau APIs. 
